                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d418">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/26448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The First Secretary of Embassy in the Soviet Union</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dickerson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kuibyshev</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >Moscow</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1942-12-12T12:00:00+03:00">December 12 [<hi rend="italic"
                            >11</hi>], 1942—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 11—10:08
                        p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1045. Soviet press comment on the scuttling of the French Fleet at Toulon<note
                        n="73" xml:id="d418fn73">Most of the French Fleet was scuttled on November
                        27, 1942, as German troops entered Toulon. A few ships escaped to North
                        African ports. Secretary of the Navy Frank Knox announced on December 8 that
                        about one quarter of the ships had fallen intact and afloat into German
                        control.</note> has been highly commendatory and has expressed great
                    satisfaction at its successful execution.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dickerson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
